params.doc:
Expected decimal places for the shipping rate. For example, if this field is 2 then the shipping rate could be: 10$, 10.1$, 10.12$ (up until 2 decimal places).
 However it can **not** be: 10.123$ (or further), and in this case the shipping option will be ignored and not provided to the user.
 When not provided, the fraction size can be anything.

docs.summary: Used for grouping line items. Sent when an item is added to a cart, checkout, or order.

members.name: catalogItemId
members.doc: ID of the item within the catalog it belongs to.

members.name: appId
members.doc:
ID of the app providing the catalog.

You can get your app's ID from its page in the [Wix Dev Center](https://dev.wix.com/apps).

For items from Wix catalogs, the following values always apply:
+ Wix Stores: `"215238eb-22a5-4c36-9e7b-e7c08025e04e"`
+ Wix Bookings: `"13d21c63-b5ec-5912-8397-c3a5ddb27a97"`
+ Wix Restaurants: `"9a5d83fd-8570-482e-81ab-cfa88942ee60"`

members.name: options
members.doc:
Additional item details in key:value pairs.

 Use this optional field to specify a variant of the item or add custom details. There are several ways to use `options`:
 + Pass specific information about the item variant in this field. For example, size and color of an item of clothing: `"options": {"Size": "M", "Color": "Red"}`.
 + Create a separate API for creating item variants that stores the details and generates a unique ID for each item variant. Then pass only the variant ID in this field. For example: `"options": {"variantId": "<VARIANT_ID>"}`.

members.name: weight
members.doc: Line item weight. Measurement unit matches the weight unit specified in `weightUnit` in the request.

members.name: sku
members.doc: Stock-keeping unit. Learn more about [SKUs](https://www.wix.com/encyclopedia/definition/stock-keeping-unit-sku).

members.name: shippable

members.name: subdivision

members.name: postalCode

members.name: addressLine2

members.name: streetAddress

members.name: code

members.name: price
members.doc: The shipping rate's price. Must align with the [currency's decimal separator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217#Active_codes).

members.name: currency
members.doc: Currency of the shipping rate price as a 3-letter [ISO-4217 currency code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217). Must align with the `currency` passed to the function under the `metadata` field.

members.name: additionalCharges
members.doc: Additional costs. For example, a handling fee for packaging fragile items.

members.name: type
members.doc: Additional charge type.

members.name: details
members.doc: Details of the additional charge. For example, `"Handling fee of $5 applied for gift wrapping"`.

members.name: price
members.doc: Cost of additional charge. For example, `12.5`.

members.name: code
members.doc: Unique code that acts as an ID for a shipping rate. For example, `"usps_std_overnight"`.

members.name: title
members.doc: Shipping rate title. For example, `"USPS Standard Overnight Delivery"`, `"Standard"`, or `"First-Class Package International"`.

members.name: logistics
members.doc: Shipping logistics.

members.name: cost
members.doc: Shipping cost.

members.name: address
members.doc: Pickup address.

members.name: pickupMethod
members.doc:
Pickup method.

Supported values:
+ `"STORE_PICKUP"`: When pickup is from the merchant's brick and mortar store.
+ `"PICKUP_POINT"`: When item is shipped to a specified pickup point.

members.name: deliveryTime
members.doc: When the item is expected to be delivered in free text. For example, `"3-5 business days"`.

members.name: instructions
members.doc: Instructions for delivery. For example, for pickup: `"Ensure to come during business hours, and please don't park in the disabled spot"`.

members.name: pickupDetails
members.doc: Pickup details. Should be returned only if order is for pickup.

members.name: from
members.doc: starting time of the delivery time slot

members.name: to
members.doc: ending time of the delivery time slot

members.name: name
members.doc: Item name.

members.name: quantity
members.doc: The number of items ordered.

members.name: catalogReference
members.doc: Reference to the item's origin catalog.

members.name: physicalProperties
members.doc: Physical properties of the item.

members.name: price
members.doc: Price of a single item after discounts.

members.name: totalPriceBeforeDiscount
members.doc: Total line item price before discounts.

members.name: priceBeforeDiscount
members.doc: Price of a single item before discounts.

members.name: totalPrice
members.doc: Total line item price after discounts. This is equal to `price` multiplied by `quantity`.

members.name: deliveryDestinationIndex
members.doc: item delivery destination index in the shipping addresses list

members.name: deliveryOriginIndex
members.doc: where the item is delivered from index in the from addresses list

members.name: taxIncludedInPrice
members.doc: whether tax is included in line item price

docs.summary:
tax info types Possible values are:
  • UNSPECIFIED
  • CPF - CPF - for individual tax payers.
  • CNPJ - CNPJ - for corporations

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_SUBDIVISION_TYPE
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_1 - State
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_2 - County
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_3 - City/town
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_4 - Neighborhood/quarter
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_5 - Street/block
  • COUNTRY - ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_0. Indicates the national political entity, and is typically the highest order type returned by the Geocoder.

Possible values are:
  • VALIDATION
  • OTHER
  • MAX
  • MIN
  • MAX_LENGTH
  • MIN_LENGTH
  • MAX_SIZE
  • MIN_SIZE
  • FORMAT
  • DECIMAL_LTE
  • DECIMAL_GTE
  • DECIMAL_LT
  • DECIMAL_GT
  • DECIMAL_MAX_SCALE
  • INVALID_ENUM_VALUE
  • REQUIRED_FIELD
  • FIELD_NOT_ALLOWED
  • ONE_OF_ALIGNMENT

Possible values are:
  • HANDLING_FEE

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_METHOD
  • STORE_PICKUP
  • PICKUP_POINT

Possible values are:
  • UNSPECIFIED_WEIGHT_UNIT - Weight unit can't be classified, due to an error
  • KG - Kilograms
  • LB - Pounds

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • ENABLED
  • DISABLED
  • PENDING
  • DEMO

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • TRASH
  • DELETED
  • PENDING_PURGE

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_NAMESPACE
  • WIX - Default namespace for UGC sites. MetaSites with this namespace will be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • SHOUT_OUT - ShoutOut stand alone product. These are siteless (no actual Wix site, no HtmlWeb). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • ALBUMS - MetaSites created by the Albums product, they appear as part of the Albums app. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • WIX_STORES_TEST_DRIVE - Part of the WixStores migration flow, a user tries to migrate and gets this site to view and if the user likes it then stores removes this namespace and deletes the old site with the old stores. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • HOTELS - Hotels standalone (siteless). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • CLUBS - Clubs siteless MetaSites, a club without a wix website. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • ONBOARDING_DRAFT - A partially created ADI website. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • DEV_SITE - AppBuilder for AppStudio / shmite (c). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • LOGOS - LogoMaker websites offered to the user after logo purchase. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • VIDEO_MAKER - VideoMaker websites offered to the user after video purchase. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • PARTNER_DASHBOARD - MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • DEV_CENTER_COMPANY - MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • HTML_DRAFT - A draft created by HTML editor on open. Upon "first save" it will be moved to be of WIX domain. Meta site with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • SITELESS_BUSINESS - the user-journey for Fitness users who want to start from managing their business instead of designing their website. Will be accessible from Site List and will not have a website app. Once the user attaches a site, the site will become a regular wixsite.
  • CREATOR_ECONOMY - Belongs to "strategic products" company. Supports new product in the creator's economy space.
  • DASHBOARD_FIRST - * It is to be used in the Business First efforts.
  • ANYWHERE - * Bookings business flow with no site.
  • HEADLESS - * Namespace for Headless Backoffice with no editor
  • ACCOUNT_MASTER_CMS - * Namespace for master site that will exist in parent account that will be referenced by subaccounts The site will be used for account level CSM feature for enterprise
  • RISE - * Rise.ai Siteless account management for Gift Cards and Store Credit.
  • BRANDED_FIRST - * As part of the branded app new funnel, users now can create a meta site that will be branded app first. There's a blank site behind the scene but it's blank). The Mobile company will be the owner of this namespace.

Possible values are:
  • OTHER - A valid option, we don't expose all reasons why site might be created.
  • FROM_TEMPLATE - A meta site was created from template.
  • DUPLICATE_BY_SITE_TRANSFER - A meta site was created by copying of the transfferred meta site.
  • DUPLICATE - A copy of existing meta site.
  • OLD_SITE_TRANSFER - A meta site was created as a transfferred site (copy of the original), old flow, should die soon.
  • FLASH - deprecated A meta site was created for Flash editor.
